\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And then downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
A - a store room and a - a big dining room which was a drawing room as well, and - and on the ground floor a kitchen. And a scullery. And below that a cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So it was four storeys in all was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were the printers shop and workshop all in that building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. At the back. Back - yes, all connected really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The living quarters then were on the first floor were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house, any relations or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no, no, not at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you tell me a bit about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
When we were little there was a nursemaid and a - and a - you know, a working girl, and the wages were about half a crown each a week. And they both slept together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did they sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They slept in a - in - in one of these rooms. But it had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 In an attic?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
No, on - with - on the floor with the other bedrooms. But it was a very cold room and it had a stone floor. And I don't know why but it was a cold room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they shared it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, shared the big bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old would they have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They'd be about seventeen - seventeen to twenty, between those - two ages, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What about doing the cleaning in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, well - we used to have a woman to do the washing on a Monday. Yes. One and nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
pence a day. And washed in the big - big wooden tub. And a copper down the yard which had to be filled - with water and - and a fire under it, an ordinary coal fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did she do all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who did the ironing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh I used to help with the ironing, I loved it, but the - oh the maid or mother - it was all done on Monday, always finished on Monday, yes. Yes, Monday. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did they eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 In the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Separately from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 After you or before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
The - when the joint was brought up to our room, the dining room - the maid came up with her plate as well and we carved some off for her you see and she took it down. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And that was the nursemaid as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was there anywhere they could sit when they were not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, only the kitchen, no - only the kitchen, that was their - place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother supervise all the housework herself? Or did she tell somebody else to tell somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no, I think - it was an understood thing, they knew what to do. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They knew the routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you feel at ease with the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Very. Very. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, a very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you address them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh we were called Miss Phyllis and Miss Beatrice, the sisters. Yes. And we just called them Kate or Edith or whatever they happened to be.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did they call your mother? And father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well I don't really remember but it might have been sir and madam but I - I don't really remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Perhaps they called your mother ma'am did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But they called you Miss Phyllis and Miss Beatrice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you feel that they were interested in you as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well - I think so, yes, I think so, they were kind. Yes, very kind. If I were - if I was late for a meal they would always have something ready. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You were telling me you used to go and talk to them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother ever give sort of moral guidance to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well I should thing so because she was a very nice person. And I think - anyone working for her would have benefited.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she strict with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Not particularly, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have rules?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, they only had to be in at - on their nights out you know, not too late, about nine to half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they allowed any free time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, sometimes they'd have an afternoon, you know, to go out and - get - look at the shops or that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother mind what they did then or did she want to know what they'd been doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, not at all, she trusted them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember if your mother or father ever mended the clothes or mended shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Not shoes, but - mother was very good - patching and mending and that sort of thing. Yes, very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would she ever make any of your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They were always bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 New?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Or someone else made them. Yes. Sometimes. Dressmakers and people like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you ever remember them being bought from a shop?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. Hats. School clothes. You know. Things that were - regulation to wear, you know school outfits, jum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414  - gym slips and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you always go to the same place for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, a corner shop called Sharpleys. Yes. Quite near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have everything there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How often would you have had new clothes, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh - we always had Sunday clothes, you know. We only wore them on Sunday and they were very nice. Yes, very nice. Very nice indeed. Good but - and then we used to wear summer dressed and winter dresses. And we changed on a certain d
ay every year whether it was hot or cold. The end of May. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And the winter ones were put away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, there wasn't that way, he wasn't gifted in that way, he wasn't domesticated, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I suppose a servant did the fires and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about decorating and repairs, improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well we had it all done by workmen, we never attempted anything like that at home, my parents didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember your father helping with you children, dressing or reading to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, cert - no, no they didn't in that - in those days. No. No, not at all, never heard of any fathers helping in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, he'd no need for it, there was always somebody else there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any jobs that you had to do regularly in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't - oh I used to - help to polish the furniture, every 
spring cleaning - time, you know, beginning of the year and - I can't remember anything special. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about your sister, did she do anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, yes - no we didn't - we - no, we didn't have to do much in the house really, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember your sister helping you to dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or do your hair or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, no, not at all, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. Bout nine o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old would you have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well you know about - fourteen or fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about when you were smaller than that, what time would you go to bed, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think about eight. I don't remember going to bed much earlier than eight, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go to bed at the same time as Beatrice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, we went - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have a bedroom of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Eventually, but not until I was older than that. No. We had a bed each in one room until we - were about thirteen or fourteen, and th
en we had a room each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And mother and father had a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have people coming to stay ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - a great deal, yes. Relations - and friends. And - later when I was about fifteen or sixteen or seventeen I used to hav
e friends come to stay, friends that I'd met - in other towns you know. Yes, we had all kinds of people to stay. And a cousin from Australia. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who's cousin was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He was a farmer. Farm. Father's side, farmer, yes. Father's, yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was that a big event?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes. Well it's a long way to come and cost a lot and he had to see a lot of relations in that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Had he emigrated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The whole family had gone. Yes. The whole family. But the one son - came over - adopted 
by another aunt and uncle, in - in England, who had no children. And so - that's how it happened. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So you've got lots of relations in Australia?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That was unusual in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Tell me about the bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well - it was heated up - it was a - I think they call them geysers or gaysers, geysers I think, had to light them and it was gas. And - bit dangerous and - bit fierce. Of course if you ran the water and had it 
there was no more to come, there was no fresh supply to come through, it came through cold when you once - got the bath, you know, full, partly full. But you couldn't just go and have a bath anytime, you'd got to think about it and light this thing and - 
wait for the water to get hot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 About once a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was there a regular bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, Saturday, and - Friday and Saturday. See, mother and father and - sister and I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about servants, did they have baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Once - once every week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well it was this big room, a dining room and - well there was a little drawing room but we didn't use it a great deal, but we had meals in this big dining room. Yes. Upstairs. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember any times when you had tea in the drawing room or any other occasion where you'd eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We used to have it sometimes in the other room. It was much smaller room. But - I can't reall
y remember. It was mostly in the big dining room where we entertained and did everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did it look out onto the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. If you looked out of the window you could see Grantham church. That - yes. Yes, quite near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember the sounds of the street at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. The butcher opposite - trying to sell his meat on Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you buy it on Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And you could hear the - you know, it was horses and carts and - and the - the dustcart and the - drays,
 they called them drays, pulled by two horses. There was always a clatter going on in the street, terrible, yes. Terribly noisy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was it hot in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I've known very hot summers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And dusty from the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where was the cooking done, can you remember what sort of a cooker it was?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 A kitchen - an old fashioned kitchen range - but we didn't - and an oven, but we had a gas stove beside it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But they used the range as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But the - the - 
they got hot water from the range, it had a - there was a boiler with a tap. So we always had hot water that way, as long as we had a kitchen fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - my mother did a lot of it. Especially on a Sunday when we had a special joint. The maid was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did mother ever help out in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh yes, a - a lot of that, yes, a lot - of work in the shop, and the library. She ran the library. There was no - there was no public library then. And people came in -
 oh a lot of people in the town - read the books and they - they had to pay tuppence a week or something like that. And it was all written down in a book. The name of the book and who it - who had taken it out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 This library was in the shop was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, it was - yes, several shelves, oh yes, several shelves - lot of books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did the books come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they were new books. Yes, new -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Bought by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. And she - from a list, you get a list and then 
you'd choose the authors and have them sent. And - as they got very old my mother used to rebind them, but if they got really very dirty and old they were thrown out. To make room for new ones, there was only a limited space. You couldn't keep adding. Bec
ause they were always full, the shelves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So she was quite important in the shop was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, she was, and she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your father go in the shop or was he in the printing works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh he was there, hovering round, yes. He didn't have to go
t the printing part at all. He didn't know anything much about the printing, he only took the orders. And - anything that he didn't understand he used to - call the - the man in the - man from the printing works at the back, and he dealt with them. Took t
he order direct. Printed a lot of bills and - notices and - you know, things like you see in a big - big - for a bazaar or for a church fete, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Tell me about the almanac that you were telling me about earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, it's a - yes, it's - it wa
s a directory, of - all the streets and - every year it had to be checked to see who had moved and who had - who - who were the newcomers and get their names, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who bought those then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well people - bought because it was a - it was very inter
esting book, it had - little stories and jokes and - and this directory and - advertisements. Yes. Trade advertisements, how he made it pay I think. And - cookery recipes and bits about the garden. Yes. And - oh I've got one at home but it's a very old on
e. I should have brought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How much did it cost, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
I think - tuppence. Tuppence, yes. It came out in - after Christmas. Somewhere in the New Year. And they sold a tremendous lot of them, yes. Stacks of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Is there anything like that today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, no. No, that - that's all been built - been pulled down, the whole house and shop and the printing works and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you tell me about the separate meals, what time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well in time to 
get to school when we were children, but only just. I should think we had breakfast about half past eight. And always a very nice breakfast. Bacon and eggs and - there weren't cereals then I think. Hardly, might just have started. But it was porridge or -
 bacon, eggs, and - fruit juices and things weren't taken then I think, we didn't think about it in those days. Coffee or tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you all eat together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have a cooked midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, yes, but not in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of things did you have for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh - a joint at the weekend, a nice big joint. Really good joint and we - then we had it cold perhaps - and rissoles and shepherds pie and all those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, lovely puddings. Steamed puddings. Yes. Jam puddings, syrup puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Milk puddings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And in the summertime always fruit. Yes. Fruit pies. Currants and raspberries and - and cherries. Oh gooseberries. Rhubarb first and then 
gooseberries, then these others followed on. But we had a lot of fruit pies and things. When we could get the fruit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of things did you have in the evening then, just a snack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well I can't really remem
ber when I was very young what we had, we used to have cheese when we were older, and - very often a piece of - ham was boiled. And lasted - kept it in the cellar and - it lasted quite a while that. And - I think we were very well fed really. I think so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember liking meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh I - some - sometimes I was not at all hungry, I didn't like some of the dinners. I didn't like the cold meat, they didn't have all the nice things in those days you know, to eat with cold meat. We didn't have a nu
mber of salads. You couldn't get them then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any garden to grow vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, but not near the house. Some distance away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Like an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did that have vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well not - yes, 
just a few. But it meant - there's a long walk to get there, quite a long walk. And - it was really too far to - to work at it every day. We didn't grow an awful lot to eat. Mostly flowers. Rose trees and - I think we had an old gardener occasionally.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Otherwise father was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 My mother used to do some. And I used to I think from what I remember, a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you keep any livestock, hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We had - had a - a cat and we had - we had different cats and I had a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Nothing to eat like pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember how many times a week you'd eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh, every day. Yes. Even on Friday. Although - we did have fish but I can't remember - having to eat fish just because it was Friday, no, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever have any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. We used to have a lot of corned beef in those days. You know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did father ever get any extra meat from anywhere like rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or a friend give him anything like pheasants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh sometimes from the country there my friend would bring a chicken, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you ever remember seeing your mother have less food so that you all could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 There was plenty to go round was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember if father had bigger portions than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I expect he did, just slightly so, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I think we were allowed to choose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Not made to eat what you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If you left anything would you be made to eat it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no, no, be - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What would your parents say if you left some food on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they wouldn't mind if it was something that I didn't really like, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, did you have to ask for it to be passed to you or could you help yourself?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I could help myself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Could you have second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. Definite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, very, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Could you bring a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When did you leave the table, did you have to wait until everybody had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I think we usually chatted a little bit, had a few words to say before we all got up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you always sit all at the same table for your meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, and always in the same place. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you sit, father at the top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Mother by the door, so that she was near the maid who brought anything in to take - father 
at the other end, and sister and I think we sat at the other side, four of us you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did father always have his meals, midday and everything, with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The maid would bring the meal in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What order were you served in, do you remember, who was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I - I think really the - the two - the two of us, the children you know, I think we had ours first. Yes, I think so, and then mother.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you never remember - you were the youngest weren't you so you won't remember about feeding little children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did the servants have the same food as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Exactly the same, and as much as they wanted, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, very. She was very intelligent. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And you got on well with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 To both of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well not always, no, I was very shy sort of person. I did keep things to myself rather. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would you ever have told your father instead of your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think either of them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about your sister, did she confide in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think she did either, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Although she was an easy person, you could have if you'd wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well they wanted us to be loving children and to respect them. And to be obedient, and we were I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And polite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they expect you to behave towards each other in any special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well we did quarrel, my sister and I I think. We didn't get on awfully well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She was a bit beastly to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, but we - we'd no great trouble over it, we got over it, got over them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Supposing you got hit in the street by some other child would your parents have said, hit back or not? Did they encourage you to fight back?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I shouldn't think so, no, I don't think so. No, they liked peace and quiet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be, what kind of a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't think they ever - said much about that. I wouldn't know what to say to that really. I think they - I think they expected
 us to be decent girls, grow up, you know to be decent women. That's all I can say really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have hopes for you of any sort? Not work because you didn't work did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I didn't work, no. Hobbies, they liked us to have hobbies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What were your hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And then you see I was allowed to take up this art business. Went - trained - in art school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That was quite unusual in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes it was. There wasn't one in Grantham. Had to go twenty-five miles to the art school at Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 About seventeen I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, twice a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How long for, how many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I should think about three years I should think. Yes. Quite three years. And was r
ather an expensive - time for my father because - there was the rail - railway fare, which - was quite expensive you know to go twice a week, twenty-five miles and back. In - in those days and he - he wasn't very off. And - and I - I was very grateful tha
t he allowed me to do it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they proud of your ability?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well they - they were so kind about that - going to that art school and - they wanted me to get on and enjoy myself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your friends thing that was very unusual?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - it was in those days, yes, it was. Yes. I was - I think I was quite favoured over that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did Beatrice do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She didn't have the same talent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When you were little, perhaps you didn't ever swear, but what would your parents have thought if you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would they have been cross?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I never heard them swear. But - it doesn't say that they didn't sometimes when I wasn't there does it. I don't think m
y mother would for a minute but my father might have done. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But you two didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When they were talking together or to their friends were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, certainly, yes. All their friends were our friends, they didn't have separate friends, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever get punished for anything, do you ever remember doing anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I - I - I don't ever remember being - being hurt or smacked but I think I was - a d
isappointment in that if I did anything that they didn't approve of you know when I was young -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How would they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well they'd just be very - serious about it all and - look a bit - sort of - upset.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You didn't ever get smacked or sent to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They'd just talk to you would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes, they might have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember how you felt about them being cross with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I used to cry. Very sensitive. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So you were upset if they were cross with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, very upset.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Would your way you grew up with your ideas about what was right and what was wrong, do you think you got those from your mother or your father or both equally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't know - I think mother had - a greater influence on me really, I think so, yes. She was closer to me than my father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When you had a birthday was it different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - a cake and some - something special for dinner perhaps. People to tea occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Christmas was more than birthdays really, because everybody had - presents then, it was more fun. Stockings hung up or pillow - no
, pillow cases. Yes, and they were always full to the top. Lovely that was. Not on the breakfast table, all - when we woke up, on - on the bed. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have special things to eat at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well we didn't have an awful lot of sweets in those days. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 A Christmas cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, Christmas cake, Christmas pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who made those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh mother. Mother, yes, made all those, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And turkey would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Turkey, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any music in your house, did anybody sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Only the - piano. My father - played the flute, but I - very seldom heard him. Yes. Very seldom heard - I think that was - really - before we were - before we were born that he - he played that, because it was in the drawer but I don'
t ever remember him playing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Mother and me sister. I wasn't much good. Sister was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever sing round the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I used to sing a bit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sorts of songs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When you come home, dear, and - and - well - yes, all that, yes - soppy ones. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When would you have had singing, in the evening or weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Singing? Any time when I wanted to and - I - I think there were - I don't think they always liked it, it - you know, it was
 - used to travel downstairs a bit the sound but anyway - no, just any old time when I wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was there a time when the family got together and had a musical evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents ever play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Don't think - we might have played card games but - don't remember. No, I don't think so.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you play with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. We had friends in, we used to - play cards, snap and - we had a lovely dolls house which we used to - have 
friends in, we - we played with that a lot. Yes. In the - in the playroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where was the playroom, what floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well that was on level - it was on the - on the - first floor, with - with the drawing room or dining room and - and - yes, that - tha
t's right, just that one, and later it was a storeroom, where they kept - things for the - for the work - printing works and for the shop, when we had grown up and didn't need the playroom. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have dolls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents read much, were there books around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, always. Mother did anyway, she read a lot. Never without a book. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What about you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, yes, we used to have books given to us at Christmas and - and - oh we used to read tho
se weekly com - comic papers, we were allowed to read those - we used to go and help ourselves to them and put them back - when we had read them, yes. In the shop. Yes. Alice Sloper. Alice Sloper. That was a - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was he a character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, he was a character. Anyone of my age would know about Allie Sloper. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
The Girls Own Paper. Yes. Yes. Or the Girls Realm, whichever - I used to have one - used to have it every month - ordered for me, yes, lovely. And - and we
 used to have - those little pink books. Tiny Tim. And - there was a - then - there was one for older children. Can't remember what it was called, you know, school - schoolboy stories. But mine was always Tiny Tim.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents have newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes what did we used to have? I don't know really. Don't remember, there'd be the Daily Mail wouldn't there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you sell newspapers in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Oh yes. Used to have them outside the door on a wire, you know. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents ever read to you, do you remember them reading aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, when - yes. When we were very little, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, not father, I remember mother reading, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did Beatrice ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I can't remember that. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 There weren't many years between you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 There weren't - no we - we weren't quite - we didn't seem to get on very well, I don't know why. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When I was little? No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You can't remember anybody in the family dying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
No, because all the - the grandparents lived right away. And when they died I wouldn't go to the funeral, be too - too far away. Don't remember ever going to any. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you taken out to visit neighbours and friends and relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - we didn't have relations in the same town. No. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Neighbours, friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Very good neighbours. And friends. In the town. And they all had - and they mostly had children about the same age. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And would they visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, whenever we liked. We were just allowed the friends in whenever we liked. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother ever take you out shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did she always do the shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I shouldn't - no, she didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who would have done it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh I think a lot of things were - were sent to us, they were probably ordered in some way or other, I don't remember her going round the shops very much. Not - not carrying heavy baskets and things, I don't remember that, I think stuff was sent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would the maid have done any shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, she didn't do any shopping I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember toing out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Only when we went a tour with him - in the car. I was quite young then, yes, I went to see my grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did she live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Ramsey. In Huntingdonshire. And - he and I went in an open car and it was very cold. We left - we set off at s
ix o'clock in the morning, and - I must have been young because I - I - I took a doll for some reason or other. I don't know whether I liked a doll when I was about twelve but - I couldn't have been any older than that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How long did you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 O
h it's - couldn't get back - you know, it was the - it took a long time - to get there. But it was slow going you know, twenty miles an hour at the most. No, we always had to stay. Stay a night or two anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would Beatrice come too or just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
I don't remember - we all - sometimes we all went but this is - this is the earliest I can remember, earliest - going with him alone when I was very young. I don't know why I went alone I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you miss your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No, not for that short time, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember any special outings with your parents, did you ever have things like Bank Holidays outings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I remember my father going - one - winter when the - the I - they flooded a - a field there and it was I - very thick ice
 and they went skating, in fancy dress, and I can remember that. Had a nightshirt and a nightcap on with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414 tassel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
. And he went skating round this place, and I went and watched him and I couldn't skate then. I learnt later on in life, but I was very young then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did mother skate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No. Don't think he - don't remember him playing cricket or football or anything like that. Don't think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Skating was quite a thing in Lincolnshire wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I beg your pardon? Yes, but you had to - you co
uldn't have any - anything but the natural - frozen ice, because - was no such thing as - those - like they have them these days. You had to wait for nature to freeze the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The long dykes, they used to have races down them didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh t
hey used to race - yes, this reminds me, they used to - race from - from Grantham to Nottingham, all along the Trent, the whole way on the ice, yes. Yes. They started at what we called our canal, that was the beginning, and that led into the Trent somehow
 and they went right to Nottingham. And you could skate the whole way when it was very cold, it has been done. Yes, that was lovely. Yes, yes. That didn't often happen though. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you make anything special of Bank Holidays do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh - shop was always closed, so everybody was able to do something. I can't remember much before we had that little car and - that was - Bank Holidays were - were great then because we got - and as well as having just Sunday for a ride we got 
the Monday as well you see, we could go a bit further. See, go a bit further to see relations. But I can't remember much what we did before we had that car. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When would you have had a car?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I can't remember the year but - it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You must have been about twelve you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
I - I think so, but it was - one of the first cars in the town, in Grantham, yes. Just my father was just crazy to get a car. Don't think he could afford it really but - we did enjoy it. Did enjoy it very much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 It was a Gladiator?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, a - a red one, and it was bought from an actress second hand. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And an actress in Grantham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. No, she - it was - I don't know where it was advertised - we bought - and I think it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was her name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Connie Edis. Connie Edis, yes. And it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And it was open?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was it cold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Very cold. Freezing cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have to wrap up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh the day when I took my doll I was perished. Oh - we - we used to buy was
h leathers, and put them on our chest underneath everything you see, over our coms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 To keep the wind out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, they were - windproof. We all had our wash}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 leathers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever go away for holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Always, yes, always to the seaside. Yes. Skegness, Mablethorpe, Sutton-on-Sea. Somewhere - the nearest seaside places usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you all go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't think my father came very often because - I don't think he could leave that business really. No, it was mother and - mot
her and the maid and - and the old dear who lived with us, old Carry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she the nursemaid?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, she was - cousin - cousin - grandfather's cousin but she lived with us. Latterly in her old age. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did she help around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I don't know, no, she used to be knitting all the time. Knitting. Spent her time knitting. She didn't do anything else, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old were you when she came to live with you, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Be about - sixteen or seventeen I suppose. She didn't c
ome to live with us until she was too old to live alone. And mother looked after her. Yes. But she - she was something like a granny but she wasn't a granny you see, took the place of a granny. Yes. Very sweet she was. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How long would you have gone away for for this holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh we used to go to our grandmother's as well as a seaside holiday. Yes. And - the girl - the young lady in the shop was allowed - she - she - she came with us to look after us, but - she had her other holiday as well,
 her own holiday, but - she came with us to - to Ransey to look after us. And she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How many weeks would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We'd have about a fortnight there with grandmother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And she was the lady who helped in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 In the shop, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How many people would there have been in the printing works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 About - six or seven. Yes, six or seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, I used to like them, I used to talk to them. Yes. Specially when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You knew how it all worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents mind you going out talking to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, not a bit, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember what you did on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, we had - we had those jumping poles at Hunstanton when we went there. Do you - we used to jump f
rom one rock to another. Do they still do that? Big long pole and you - it's fun that was. You jump - ever such a long way, from one - rock to another, it was fun that was. They were sold specially. Yes. In Hunstanton. And we used to make sandcastles and 
- bathe a bit and that sort of thing. And always go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12060408\charrsid5979414 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
ierots on the - in the evening. On the pier. That was at Skegness on the pier. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That was a treat was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh it was super because there was no cinema. Nothing else. It was lovely to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have them on the beach as well in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think so. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or Punch and Judy people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They used to make a - they used to have it - have them on the pier years ago usually because they had a proper stage there. And prop
er seats for the audience to sit in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How much did it cost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I should think about sixpence wouldn't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember how you spent Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. I used to take my penny into the market - and spend it at the penny stall. Yes, penny stall, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was on the penny stall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh lovely things. Little dolls, little horses, things for the dolls house. And mouth organ, all those funny little things. Yes. Penny.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That would be in the morning would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you play in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, we used to play with the dolls house. Yes, and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about Sundays? How would a Sunday go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We used to go to church nearly always. In the morning. And - we went for a walk after - after church, always, you 
know, some little walk Sunday or - in our best clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Would all the family go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
No. Father sang in the choir. Mother used to be cooking Sunday dinner usually. I - I think she went once or twice, but - we usually went with our friends, other little girls. Yes. Can remember that very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You wouldn't have to go again in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I never remember going to evening church, no, not when I was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you allowed to play on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They weren't strict about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. Nothing like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was this Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was there a Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, there was no - as far as I remember there wasn't any Sunday school in those days. No, don't remember Sunday schoo
l. I didn't go to that sort of school though you know, I went to private school so I wouldn't know quite what happened at the other schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Sunday school's usually attached to church isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well, yes, I think it would be. I don't remember about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have any other activities the church organised, like clubs or temperance group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, that - not - I wasn't connected with anything like that, no. No, I didn't - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you say grace at home at mealtimes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well we di
d, yes, we did for - I - I don't know when it stopped but we did used to say grace early on when I was very little, but I can't remember - I'm sure it - something happened that it wasn't continued after a certain time, and I don't know why. I can't tell y
ou why really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did father say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. I don't why that happened, it must have happened in a lot of families though. Don't you think so? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 It wasn't when father died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well I think we were left - to decide for ourselves. I can't remember when I was very tiny what happened. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You never had family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your father have an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, Conservative. Always Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We were all Conservatives, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Why do you think he was a Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well you either had to be Conservative or Liberal. And we were always Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You don't remember him saying anything about why he was Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember him or your mother voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I knew we - we had colours to wear. Yes. Red. Yes. Rosettes on - election day. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Which election would that be, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - the general elections, I don't remember local ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I can't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did father work for the party at all, did he help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I should say that the did more printing for the Conservatives than he did for the Libe
rals, because I think the Liberals would go to a - a Liberal printer if there was such a thing. There could have been. There - there was as a matter of fact. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you know if he - do you know if your mother voted Conservative because your father did, or did she have her own political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh no, we were all the same, all - you took - you did that as a matter of course, you didn't think really, if your father - voted Conservative well you did and your mother did and we all did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they take part in any political activity other than at election time, was he a member of the Conservative Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I think he was, I think, I wouldn't be sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he go to any political meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When your parents weren't working how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Now let's see. I wonder now. It's going back a bit isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they do things together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so, neither of 
them did much gardening and - no, I think they liked to rest when there was a holiday because it's hard work rather when the - the shop and the printing works there. It was very tiring and Saturday was an awful day. A long day. Very tired Saturday night a
lways. And all the market people came in Saturday from all the villages around. It was very hard work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did mother have any interests outside the home of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can't remember. He was a Mason, my father. She went to Masonic things. And - no, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did she have friends of her own? Apart from his. Or did they have friends together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, they - we - no, we were all - all friendly family you know, all the - friends were everybody's friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She didn't have one best friend of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You had the neighbours didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Neighbours there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What were they called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Mr and Mrs Rowel. Grocer. He was a grocer, yes, next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they pop in and out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Not a great deal. Not a great deal, but they were friendly, nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents ever go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did father ever go to the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think he did before I remember. When he was a - young married man, I don't - don't - not
 after I remembered anything about him he didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did mother ever go to the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You think your father belonged to the Conservative Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I know he did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he go there for a drink and a game of cards or something?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You said he skated but you can't remember him taking part in any other sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he bet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember them belonging to any sort of savings club, like for paying the doctor's bills or funeral or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can I remember what? Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You said you didn't get on especially well with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have a best friend of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - I mean - I had more than one. One after the other. Yes. Do you want their names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, where did they come from, were they neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, well one was - the daughter of an ironmonger and - yes, she was a nice girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did you play when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well didn't play in the street. No, we played - we played in the school playground, that was very nice big playground. And we didn't do that sort of playing around like the children these days, we - we went for wa
lks. And - played in the back yard a bit. But not in the street ever, people didn't in those days. Don't know why. Still - the children didn't seem to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go to your friends' homes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. Went to tea and - parties, there was always a b
irthday party, and a Christmas party to go to, and - we - we gave them - ourselves as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember any of the games you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Postman's knock. Hunt the slipper. Consequences. And - and sometimes card games. But - what were the ot
hers now, I don't know, I've forgotten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever play any rough games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, we didn't play rough games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You never got dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you free to play with anyone you chose or did your parents ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no, we were allowed to play with any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you belong to any youth clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Don't think there were any. No. I'm sure there weren't in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any hobbies besides your painting and drawing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Don't remember anything. No, I didn't, no, I didn't collect stamps. No. Oh cigarette cards we collected for a time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did they have on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well they had - Kings and Queens, the Royal Family and - cricketers, 
footballers, coats of arms. Oh actresses and actors. Yes. Yes. But - oh - the Dare Sisters Phyllis Dare and what was her other - the elder sister - Zena. Zena and Phyllis Dare, and they - they had their - they pic - our postcards then that we bought to se
nd away were actresses and they - they were on them, before Gladys Cooper, long before. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you keep postcard albums?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If somebody sent you a postcard you'd stick it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 As well as a photo album?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You liked going for walks, did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. Never could ride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you ride now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you take a part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Tennis. Loved tennis. And - there was a time when I played cricket. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go to any theatres or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, we had a theatre in Grantham. Just in the winter season. And we went to plays and - the boys at the Grammar school gave their plays - on the stage and - and the - and our - and our - and the girls 
from our school - you see, and we - we had to try and dress up girls as boys, and the Grammar school had to try and dress up boys as girls, so it was a bit of a muddle. And we used - yes, it was a bit difficult wasn't it, yes. And - I used to go and see s
u
ch - I used to see - Judy Campbell's mother, and her husband, they were a pair. Actor and actress, they were wonderful. Yes. They used to - they used to come on at Grantham stage - and - in things like East Lynn and - oh they were - very dramatic she was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever go to music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. The theatre put on musical things but - we wouldn't call it a music hall. No, they didn't call it - no, oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were there any cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The first cinema I went to w
as - in Grantham fair. It was a side - instead of a side show they had a - a little tent with a cinematograph, and it showed - Maria Martin in the Red Barn, and it was horrible. That's the - remember that was the first thing I ever saw on a - on - cinema.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old were you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 About - thirteen I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was it a big fair Grantham fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, very old fashioned fair. Round-abouts, and - fortune telling shows and - and - they sold Grantham rock. And what else? Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What time of year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Switchback - always in March. Yes. And one year I wasn't allowed to go in because they'd had the smallpox. And we weren't allowed to go in.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. It increased as I grew up. About - sixpence and then perhaps a shilling. Don't think it went much more than two shillings ever. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have it regularly every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Suppose I used to buy some sweets. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You didn't sell sweets in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Just the printers and books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you sell books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. You could order books as well. The schools used to come and order their books. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was the shop like, can you describe it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes - counter behind - a - a rack in front to take all these papers, you know, weekly papers, and - a case with - pencils in. And then a - a -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did anyone outside the house come in to help your mother look after her house or family, say when she was ill or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No, I don't think she was ill like - in that way. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she a very strong lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did she look like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Very pretty - when she was young, yes. And good features. And a - nice sort of soft kind of face with - grey hair - latterly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of dresses did she wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh the long ones to start with, trailing on the - ground. Yes. Then they gradually got shorter. Never very short. No cardigans in those days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did they keep warm then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
They didn't seem - we didn't seem to have cardigans. Warm dresses in the winter and thin dresses in the summer. There was a shawl to put on if you - you know, if you felt a bit poorly, just put a shawl round shoulders and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What were the dresses made of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Best dresses, it was satin. You know, the shiny satin. And lace. And prints, lovely prints for - summertime, for day dresses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did your father look like, did he have a beard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, he was dark. I don't thi
nk he had a moustache or a beard, very dark, I never remember him being anything but dark, and - rather a big man. Tall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was mother little or tall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She - no, medium, she wasn't tall, no, medium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents have regular friends that they saw very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. She didn't ever go out to - tea parties, coffee parties, they didn't have them. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 There were no special friends they saw more of?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. I think - have an idea she played bridge sometimes with people, but I - couldn't quite remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Just her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Not father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, he used to play as well. Now - on Sunday evening, we always had a very very nice supper. Laid - the maid laid it and she came in and cleared it when she got - came in at half p
ast nine, but it really was a big spread. And we had - always had two friends in every week. A - a man who had had no home and he'd lost his job, he was very hard up and his - his wife lived with her brother in the country on a big farm, and he cycled hom
e
 on a tricycle. He went home on Friday evening and he came back on Sunday evening and he came in and had supper with us. And - and he - he was very hot - with preadling this thing, and he - he was sent up to the bathroom with a big bath towel and he just 
stripped and washed if he wanted to, and then he came down and was ready for his pipe and his supper. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you get to know him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh he was an old family friend, lived in Huntingdon and, you know, long before I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How far had he had to cycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
About eight miles. Yes. I don't remember what he did in the very bad weather, but I remember he got very hot when it was this sort of weather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He worked in Grantham during the week did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He worked at Ruston and Hornsby. And he - 
he was what they call a - he - he - when the men clocked in - something he had to - every man had to say or give him a ticket or something - as they arrived and he had to make note of it. And he got a pound a week for it. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he live in lodgings during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. The whole pound went to the lodgings. Didn't have anything. I expect the - I expect he was given some pocket money. And every Christmas he brought us - half a stilton cheese for a present. Yes. And he used to - with his s
upper he used to drink a bottle of beer and oh he did used to love it. He just used to sit and read, we brought him up all the papers that he wanted out of - from the shop. He loved them, he went through the whole lot. Illustrated London News and - Punch 
and everything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he talk to you children, were you friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old a man was he then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He about the same age as my father I should think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who else, you said two people came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Then the other was
 a - a man - he had - I don't think - he was not mar - he'd never married, and - I don't think he had any home, he only had lodgings, from what I remember, all his life, and they both worked - Ruston and Hornsby had a place in Lincoln as well. Yes, and I 
think - I think he worked in Lincoln some of the time. I can't remember very - clearly about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they both came every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But he was a peculiar looking man, a little bit like - van Gogh with, you know - pointed face and a bit gingery so
rt of thing. Yes. He was very keen on me. Oh very. He was chasing me all the time. But my sister insisted not - he said she - he's really - likes me better. And of course - but in the end he didn't get either of us. No, there's a - of course he was so old
 for me, but at that age you - you get a - you get - these - ideas into your had that - everybody who talks to you makes if they're really very keen on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You quite liked older men at that age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We talked about having friends in to the house didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they just came in whenever they liked. Whenever they liked, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they'd have a cup of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they your mother's friends particularly or your father's friends or just friends of both of them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh well, there was one person they liked very much indeed, she was very beautiful, but she - her hus - she'd married - and her husband - had left her with a little girl. And - she - so we - that -
 this is before she had the little girl, she - she was in the George Hotel. She was very beautiful. I don't know what she did, whether she was receptionist or what.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She came often did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And father gave her ten shillings every Christmas for a present. And ten shillings was a lot in those - oh she was very sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your parents go out to visit friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We used to go out to - to this - farm where - old Mr Bryant I was telling you about who came in for supper - we went to the same far
m where he spent his weekends. And it was a house very like this of yours. Lots of ground, but a real farmhouse. Yes. And - when they killed the pig we always had a - a pork pie I think. But they ate so much pig all at once, they all made themselves ill. 
S
tarted off with spare rib and then went through the whole lot. Our friends was always ill when they'd killed a pig. She was the daughter of this little - man who worked at Horsnby's. Yes, but - she wasn't there all the time, a - an uncle - a doctor in Lon
don brought her up quite a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Because the wife was dead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh no. But the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 She was the one who lived on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They - you see, the uncle didn't want - them all there really, he - he - he gave his his sister - this home and he 
- he - and - but the - May, the daughter, spent a lot of time in London with this doctor. But Kathleen the younger one was always - and there's ten years difference between those two girls. May was - my age, and Kathleen was ten years younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So the family was quite split up really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 People say that you had to make your own amusements in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh you did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of things did you do? What did your parents do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Mother sat and played patience every night. She loved it. And she - she knitted. But she was a great reader. Yes. Good - nice books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about father, what did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Don't remember really. I don't know what he did in the evenings, I can't remember, I expect he had a lot to 
do - on the booking - book keeping to do and things like that. But he didn't go out a lot, didn't leave us, but I don't quite remember what he did. 'Cos you see he died and I'm thinking about mother really when she was on her own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old were you when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - I think it was - just - before the war or the first year of the war. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He was quite a young man then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember how you thought of the various classes, what you called them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, we were 
a bit snobbish weren't we in those days. Not really. I mean we were always nice to people, my mother and father were, it didn't matter who they were, but there was that feeling that - the doctors were a little bit above us, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You'd say there was an upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. Doc - the doctors and - oh, you know - they used to ride their horses, the Hutchinsons - a brewer - the brewery, yes, and they used to go riding their horses and they - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who else was in the upper class, was the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
No, I don't think so. All these people - now, the Hornsby's you see. Yes. Yes. And - Avelin and Barfus came on much - much later. I can't remember anybody, oh of course you know there was Beaver Castle used to visit. Yes. And that was the Manners. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They would have been aristocrats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, we used to - that was a very good outing there, to go to Beaver Castle, it's about - eight or nine miles. And then - then - the nearer one was - you know, you've heard of Belton Park, beautiful, it was Belto
n House. I hope I'm getting the names right, the family living there was - don't quite know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did they get their money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't know. Landowners I should think wouldn't you, I should think, and the park was huge. Oh yes. Just along - terra
ce, big gates, and you walked right up, and it was quite a long walk to the house, think about two miles. But people were allowed to have picnics there. Very nice indeed. You could - you - you could - walk, and then just go through the gates and you could
 sit down anywhere with all your picnic stuff and they - they didn't mind a bit. And there was a lodge - where you could get hot water. Very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What class would you say you were, your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What do you say the -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What class would you say your family belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - just a little bit below the - doctors and solicitors and the - people like - would you call it middle class, I don't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If they were upper middle I suppose you'd be middle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. We always had that feeling the
n - in those days - you never got to know those people above you very well. No, you'd meet them but you - there'd always be that barrier between you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of people belonged to your social class? Other trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8325879\charrsid5979414 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - no the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or was the printer a bit better than the butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
We were better. We didn't mix with the bakers and the butchers and - no, we didn't have anything to do with them, no. Don't know why but they were just a bit lower still you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The printing was a craft as well as a trade wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. Yes, and you'd be surprised at the people that wents in and - into - talked to mother and father. Lady Diana Mullis would go in and - and say what she wanted. You see, and asked to see Mr Palmer. It was very nice. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So really just below you were the butchers and bakers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. And mother came of a very good family, she was always picked out as a - what in those days was a lady. Yes. Every inch of her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was her family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they were farmers and - all sorts of things like that. What did - anything else they did. I can't think what else -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she a better family than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. I think, just a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you think she thought she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, she wasn't like that, but I - I think people would think so really, he was quite a gentleman. But - she was - you see, the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8325879\charrsid5979414 aunty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
 I - and she was so - very much the lady and mother was her sister, and they did belong to that - certain type of - family and people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who would be below the trades}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8325879\charrsid5979414 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 people do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, there was - well we didn't have any other - there - we weren't in an industrial area really, not in those days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who were the poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well, the people - people who worked in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8325879\charrsid5979414 H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 ornsby's you know, doing all the rough work and - people working on the roads in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were there many poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, not an awful lot. Just certain little streets. You'd always find a whole lot of them - Newgate, Swinegate, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they look poor, were the children ragged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, they didn't have - they didn't have any social - you know, any - any - any allowances or anything. They only had what their mother and father earned, that was all. And sometimes it wasn't much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you think they lived reasonably well or did they waste what they had got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I - I don't know, I don't think they could afford - well meat was quite cheap then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember any drunkenness in the streets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Very seldom, no I don't think so. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember - you say the maid called you Miss Phyllis, do you remember - and mother and father were called sir and madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 By some people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well I don't really - I think she used to say Mrs Palmer. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did the men in the works call your father sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 OH yes. Sir, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have to call anybody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or curtsey to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who were considered the most important people in Grantham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The Mayor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was he like, what was his name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
He had to be a councillor of course, he was voted - got him in. And that was a great day. Elections and voting for the Mayor and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of a man would the mayor be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well - to begin with in the early days he was - quite good class person, probably one of these people like the - as I - we've been talking about. You know, brewer - perhaps one from the head of the breweries and - and then, you know, as years went 
on it was just a question - I know we did have quite ordinary people and - we couldn't understand it to start with, a very - rather against it. 'Cos we didn't think that - it had been so long the other way, that - but they did, they got in - they were vot
ed in. I suppose they did the work all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who else was important in the town, the other councillors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, councillors and - there was the - people who - tanners you know, a terrible smell when you went by there. You know, the leather, tanning
 - tanning leather. Now what was - forget their name now. But it - oh it was a foul smell. Yes. Yes. In a big place, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about the vicar, you haven't mentioned him much, was he very important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They didn't have - no, they didn't call to see us, I don't think we went to church enough for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was the difference between the people who went to church and those who went to chapel, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Very - the church people thought - we thought we were a little bit above the 
chapel people, why I don't know. Silly wasn't it. My friend went to chapel and - and - Congregational but - I liked her very much. But I think the church then in those days was the most important. And you see it was such a beautiful church. It was heavenl
y, beautiful place to to go into. And you didn't - in the chapel it was very different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well - I don't really know. Quite a number. There was the - there was the Wesleyans. All these little chapels were all dot
ted about. Peculiar. Oh I don't know who - I never met them really, only this one friend of mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different sort of groups? Like some craftsmen and some rougher families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well - they did eat differently. Yes, they bought - they didn't have the money to buy - I know in the shops you'd see them come in and ask for - you know, scrag end and - you know - lamb and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember if there was any difference between a craftsman, like a carpenter, and a labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes. Very good - very good - joiners and carpenters and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They were more respected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They probably had a better standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they earn more money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 They agreed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, they did, that seemed to be on everything more or less, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was it ever possible to move from one class to another? Either to better yourself or to sink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well they did you know. Through money. Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember one family that did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they could be quite common. No, I
 don't - not just thinking off hand now. We used to rather resent it you know when they - got up like that and left us behind. Through their money and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you think people forgot that they'd come up because of money or do you think they were always known to be jumped up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I think - no, I don't - I think they were - but they were never quite respected like the original families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did people sink down through spending the money in the wrong way or bad luck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they were more careful. T
hey didn't fritter their money away in those days. You only bought something when it - you either wanted it very badly or it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You said about your mother that she was a real lady, people talked about real ladies and real gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Well they've said - told me so often since - not now, but when people were still living who knew her. They said that she - she really was, she - she could have talked to the Queen, she was such a lady. Yes. And she was intelligent, very. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That was more to do with the family they came from really than to do with money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh it was, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Your mother used to sit her on her knee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, little - she used to always draw little girls for me, little girls doing - sitting, little girls p
laying with dolls, and - she didn't tell me stories but she could draw these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 That's where you get it from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Tell me about the time when you got tails from the guillotine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - the horses tail? Well we - we were childr
en, my sister and I, we - we were rather - we - we invented things and we worked things out for ourselves and we - we saw all these strips of - off from the guillotine, they were about half an inch quarter of an inch, and long, quite long, about three qua
r
ters of a yard long. Well the - the length of a - is it an imperial sheet of - well, they were long, and all colours, beautiful. So there - once somebody had a bright idea about tying the top up, onto a long string and typing - we tied them round our wais
t and then we ran around with these tails - pretending we were horses. Had a lot of fun with things like that. I think my sister was very good at thinking out things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she inventive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Can't think what else we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. They used to walk the streets at night. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you think of them, were they feared?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh we weren't told in those days that if we were naughty the policeman was coming f
or us, we weren't, but other children were, yes. If you're not good the policeman will come for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you think the policemen in those days were harder on people or better towards people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, in our - in Grantham there wasn't a lot of violence and - crime or anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they friends of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. Very - very friendly, yes. Oh my father was a fireman as well. Yes. I've just remembered that. Yes. I think - yes, he was called out occasionally. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever go down to the fire station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Remember his helmet now. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you ever go down to the fire station?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. Don't think we had an awful lot of fires.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You owned all your property didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was there ever any struggle to make ends meet in the house do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. Don't ever remember getting into debt at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or talking about how you were going to pay the bills or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember if there was anybody in the district who was disapproved of very strongly by everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Disapproved of what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If people disapproved of them very strongly, any particular family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I don't think so. Some were a bit snobbish and didn't approve of things the othe
rs did, but I can't tell you what it was they did actually, can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 There was no family that was so awful that they had to be got out of the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 OH no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Sometimes in villages they used to get them out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you ever given lessons by a governess or a tutor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, went - I went to school when I was four and I was the youngest at that time, and I sat on a high stool. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 At the private school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was it small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh - Spartan - it w
as all - the children, the boarders were - oh it was a terrible school really, but - the boarders were very badly fed. And the rooms were cold. Bedrooms were cold. And every -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Where did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 We used to take our lunch, I'll tell you in
 a minute where they came from, we used to take our lunch, something nice and the - the boarders were - the maid in the school brought a plate of - slices of bread, and a - and some glasses of water, and that's all the boarders had for their mid morning -
 and it - I think I used to give sometimes take them things and I - I go very fond - fond of some of the boarders and I used to have them to stay, they were all - they were from the country around. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Farmer's children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they miserable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they miserable, did they seem unhappy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
I think they were - oh I think they were a bit, they looked - they looked - they didn't look healthy and well, they looked as though they were half starved. I don't know 
what the parents - whether the parents didn't know or what, but it was all you could do in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they had to pay to send them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you start by going all day or just in the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I should think when I was very little it was the morning. Can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did your mother take you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I can't remember that part. Unless -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You said that your mother never pushed a pram?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. She was frightened, scared. Never took us out at all. Tha
t's why they had a nursemaid. But we didn't keep on a nursemaid after we were - I suppose a nurse - we only had a nursemaid until we were about - well al - school age, perhaps, going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Why was she frightened to take you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I don't kno
w. She had no confidence like that. She was sort of person who would never - you could have never told - she - she didn't ride a bicycle and she wouldn't have driven a car. You know, even if it - there had been cars, she was terribly nervous of things lik
e that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And yet she was very capable in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What did you feel about your teacher, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, the headmistress was - horrid. You see, I wasn't clever at school. Not in the way that she wanted me to be. I never
 had a chance to develop anything in the arts. It was all - horrid stuff, learning dates and - and having to stand up and say - bits of poetry and I always forgot it after the first line. No, she didn't like me. But I liked my music teacher. Although I ne
v
er - I never - you know, I didn't play well, I wasn't music - but she was just a nice person, I - she's the one I used - to have in for tea and - and took her out rides in the car, remember father taking her for a ride. Yes. And I kept up a correspondence
 with her until she died. Yes. Very nice person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You went on writing to your mother very regularly didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, twice a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Right until she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 It would be a bit difficult when you were on your own in the war and the children were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh I don't know, I always found - found time to write. I used to send a very long letter about the details and she used to send - very wonderful letters back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember how naughtiness was punished in the school? Was it just girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. I - I think I can even remember - them being put in a corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were they ever hit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 But they weren't - no, no. No. But she was very beastly I think when I look back, the headmistress. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was she a spinster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Hard looking woman. Sort of - oh - I shuddered when she looked at me, I was so frightened of her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I suppose she'd be in - forty - I can't tell you really. She seemed old - she seemed horrible to me and she seemed old 
and - but she couldn't have been. She was clever. Oh yes. And there are some girls - even I know them now, who thought she was wonderful, because she had favourites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 The bright ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, and some of the bright ones I know now and - especially o
ne and - and she - she lived with Miss Page, was a companion to - her name was Miss Page, she lived with her until she died. And they were very happy but then she just happened to be the one who fitted in that's all, with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 If you didn't fit in she was beastly to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 It was all girls and it was private?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Walked, it was just up the High Street in Grantham. Yes. Very short distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Som
etimes. Yes. If she was cross with me about anything she said, I'm not walking up - you along that - that side of the street and I'll go this, and we went like that you see and - and - we met at the school. But that school - I was wondering the other day 
- I couldn't think what had happened to that school and - and it suddenly - I thought, it should be there, what's happened, and I suddenly remembered it's the big cinema. Yes. On St Peter's Hill. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. We had from twelve 'til - two, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, were they very particular about manners and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Oh yes. And honesty and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh yes, they - and there was - in that school there was a back staircase, wooden - old wooden back staircase where - all the girls had to go up but - all the teachers went up the carpeted stairs the other side, and you were never allowed 
on there, I - I was very - naughty once, I - I ran up there and thought I wouldn't be seen but - I think they caught me at the top. And the boarders all had to go up the back stairs and they went up to these awful - went right up to the school rooms and t
hen on the top - awful bedrooms, cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can you remember if there were any gangs or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you go to another school after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Well it - not - I left there and went to the art school - Nottingham. Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old did you leave school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I should think I went to Nottingham about sev - sixteen perhaps seventeen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So you were a long time at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was it called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Fernside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did they teach you to be ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have any - did you ever think it could have been a better education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, I was quite satisfied, I knew I wasn't very bright but it didn't worry me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you think perhaps that they should have brought out your artistic talent a bit more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
They didn't - well you see, the drawing we did then, you had a drawing book and you sat round a table and you had a - a cone or a cylinder to draw, now - can you think of anything more boring. Horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You must have loved it when you went to Nottingham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes I did. I was in my element then, yes I really was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were there many girls like you at art school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No, they - people hadn't taken up art then. I - I was - I - I had two friends there and - just the three - no,
 two - three of us all sat together and we - we were told when we arrived - that Mr Stevens, the man who - taught us, he said, could - could you draw something you've seen coming to school this morning, and I - I had plenty of opportunities because I - I'
d been on the train to start with and I'd walked to the station, then I had a long walk, you see, from the train 'til the - to the school. I had plenty of things I could draw. It was fun. Yes. My -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were there any boys in the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No. No
. And then - I didn't get any further than drawing - in - in the next year if I'd stayed I would have started painting I expect. But I found it too much for me, the trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14483621\charrsid5979414 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 ling. I wasn't very strong at that time and - had to give it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Were you courting by this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Had you many boy friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did your parents feel about boy friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh they liked the one that I have now married. He - they thought the world of him. And my - and the other old dame at the sc
hool - there was an old dame as well as this very - young one, a Miss Hancock, and she met me in the town one days and she said, you know - you - you're doing very well for yourself aren't you, because I - I had this husband was - rather above me you see 
in station and she - and I thought it was not very nice but - certainly couldn't - she thought I ought to have married somebody in a trade. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What were grandad's people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He was surveyor. Yes. County sur - County Surveyor, yes, and he - very handsome man and you could see him walking -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14483621\charrsid5979414  home for his lunch everyday sw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 inging his stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I met him at a whist drive. I had known him as a little boy, because we all used to go to the fancy dress balls and things togethe
r. But only as children. And then I met him and decided that he was very nice at this whist drive. And I think we were both about sixteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about Beatrice, did she have a boyfriend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, she had one or two. And - as a matter of fact - sh
e had a - she met another boy and we - we - the four of us went out together and the one I now married and this boy, they - they tossed up to see who should take Beatrice and who should take Phyllis, and I - I was lucky, I - I might have had Frank Trotter
. I'm glad I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What happened to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh it didn't last that - with my sister, no, didn't last at all. It's funny that wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh I didn't - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Or didn't you have an engagement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes, but I don't remember when it was, didn't worry for a few years, we were too young. He used to have his walk every night. All weathers. Yes, used to meet every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When you left school did your relationship with your parents change?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How about your sister when she left school and you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Can't remember. Don't think she did anything else when she left school, I'm sure she didn't in fact. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did she treat you as a little girl when you were still at school and she wasn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No I don't think so, but we - we weren't very close as sisters. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 By this time did you have one special friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 I think we had two or t
hree. Two or three different - we'd have one friend to - to play, you know, a certain game or go out - no, we'd have a different friend who wanted to do something else, you see, that - that's how it worked out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 In your spare time, how did you spent the day when you weren't going to art school, when you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Oh, do little jobs. I didn't do a lot - I didn't do much housework. I - I'd clean the brass or the silver, I liked doing that. And - I don't think I did anything in the shop at all, c
an't remember. No. I might - I might have got the morning coffee for the staff, they all came in and - and had it or it was taken to them. I didn't do much cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you do any sewing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Didn't do that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you make any clothes, you're good at it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
I didn't start that - making clothes until - I don't think I did much dressmaking 'til I was married. Can't remember, no. She used to buy material then go to a little dressmaker. Yes. In the back street. It was very nice. I know - I 
know that some of the girls had very beautiful clothes, there was - two old dears - a very exclusive shop and they used to make - turn out the most wonderful clothes for children. Yes. But they couldn't afford them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You used to bring friends home, that was welcomed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And they didn't ever say, I don't want you to bring so and so home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old were you when you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Twenty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you save up to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Oh yes. Yes. I had p
lenty - I had plenty for the trousseau and for - and I had a lovely stock of - -f linen to start with because it - it had been handed down. Real homespun linen, from my Uncle Phil. My mother had a big chest in the - in the attic and it was full of these l
ovely sheets, and they were waiting for him to have a home his own, and he never had one. He always lived with his sister. So I used those for a long time when I was first married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Do you remember your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Tell me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 W
ell - it was - I'd been to the doctor's wedding about a few weeks before and I - I so loved - they played the Spring Song. And of course their wedding was in the spring but I insisted on having the Spring Song. And I knew the organist, I'd been trying to 
l
earn to sing with them, and he said, why do you want that? And I said, I just want it because I love it. And he - he played it for me you see, and his fee was a guinea, and he - when I gave him the - the guineas he wouldn't take it, he said, oh no, I'd li
ke you to have that as a wedding present. But my husband was in uniform and I was in - in white and a veil and a train, little train. And - two bridesmaid but they - unfortunately they weren't dressed alike but it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was your sister a bridesmaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes. And my husband's sister was bridesmaid. Yes, Auntie Doris, yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have lots of guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes, we had a - an uncle who came - now - my husband's - uncle was - married us, because he was the vicar, he came 
over to marry us which was very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was this uncle John?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Uncle John, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Who'd been a missionary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. He came over and married us and - we had it at home, it was a very big dining table, it just - it just took everybody, you know
, just - I can't tell you how many but it - we were just all round it with the love - with some lovely food, very nice, and champagne and everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. We set off and we got as far as Doncaster, we had a little 
car. Doncaster. And - the hotel was called the Denham. Yes. And then we went on to Harrogate. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How long did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 A week I think. And I had to pull my husband's - boots off, he wore officer's uniform, he couldn't get them off. He hadn't 
got that thing that you put your heel in and - I had to pull his boots off. Oh he looked very smart. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he have to go back in the army then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 And you went on living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. I'm afraid he went up to the front lines then
, I wasn't very happy. But his main job was driving a general around. Yes. Yes. And he was sent up to the front lines. Some reason or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 So by 1918 you were still living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 How old was he when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 When he married? A few months younger than me, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You were much of an age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 What was his job before you were married, before he went in the army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 He went to - Ruston and Nornsby's. Ten shillings a week he had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Was he a sort of an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. And he had to go to - Burlitz I think their name was for - the name of the people who taught languages in Nottingham. Is that right? Burlip. He - he was - he took - he was learning French and German - at - night school, in Nottingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 You went to live in France didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 
Yes. Yes. Because it was necessary for him to have these languages, you see, and so he - he look - learnt - they taught - he was taught in Nottingham, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5792032 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Did he like the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3621955 PP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6226744\charrsid5979414 Yes. Yes.
\par }}